{"segment_id": "00080", "page_num": 80, "segment": "Figure 5.8: The Three Basic Metrics of Flow on a CFD\n\nNumerically, these calculations look like Figure 5.9:\n\nFigure 5.9: Numerical Representations of the Metrics of Flow\n\nAs I mentioned in Chapter 2, it is possible to segment WIP into several\n\nconstituent types (as also mentioned in Chapter 3 on Little’s Law). CFDs\nare no different. As you may have guessed by now, when we collect our\nflow data, we can either look at that dataset as a whole in a CFD, or we can", "source_file": "Actionable_Agile_Metrics_for_Predictability_An_Introduction_-_Daniel_S_Vacanti.pdf", "extraction_method": "pdfminer", "ocr_used": false, "has_table": false, "chapter_num": "5", "chapter_title": "Flow Metrics and CFDs", "section_num": null, "section_title": null, "l1_summary": "Figure 5.8: The Three Basic Metrics of Flow on a CFD Numerically, these calculations look like Figure 5.9: Figure 5.9: Numerical Representations of the Metrics of Flow", "l2_summary": "Figure 5.8: The Three Basic Metrics of Flow on a CFD Numerically, these calculations look like Figure 5.9: Figure 5.9: Numerical Representations of the Metrics of Flow As I mentioned in Chapter 2, it is possible to segment WIP into several constituent types (as also mentioned in Chapter 3 on Little’s Law). As you may have guessed by now, when we collect our\nflow data, we can either look at that dataset as a whole in a CFD, or we can", "prev_page": {"page_num": 79, "segment_id": "00079"}, "next_page": {"page_num": 81, "segment_id": "00081"}, "extended_fields": {"has_code": false, "has_formulas": true, "has_diagram": true, "has_list": false, "has_citations": false, "key_terms": ["figure", "flow", "metrics", "look", "mentioned", "chapter"], "content_type": "theory", "domain": "management", "complexity": "intermediate", "companies": [], "people": [], "products": [], "technologies": ["CFDs"], "frameworks": [], "methodologies": [], "programming_languages": [], "has_best_practices": f